<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Uninstallation</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>##intro.</p>
            <p><i>TODO step by step description</i></p>
            <p>To uninstall the Horizon Plugin, proceed as follows:</p>
            <ol compact="no">
                <li>
                    <p>Log in to the OpenStack node on which the OpenStack Horizon service is installed.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Remove the symlinks:<codeblock>rm &lt;horizon_dir>/openstack_dashboard/enabled/_50_admin_add_monitoring_panel.py
rm &lt;horizon_dir>/openstack_dashboard/conf/monitoring_policy.json</codeblock></p>
                    <p>Replace <codeph>horizon_dir</codeph> by ### </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Remove the line with the instruction to append site-packages in the wsgi file:</p>
                    <p>Open the <codeph>django.wsgi</codeph> file. It is located in  <codeph>&lt;horizon_dir>/openstack_dashboard/wsgi/</codeph></p>
                    <p>delete the line</p>
                    <codeblock>sys.path.append("&lt;monasca_ui_dir>/lib/python2.7/site-packages/")</codeblock>
                    <p>and save.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Delete created files:</p>
                    <codeblock>rm -rf &lt;monasca_ui_dir>/monasca_ui</codeblock>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Also you will need to remove Python system path appended to manage.py if you needed to add it to make monasca-ui run properly.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Restart the Apache Server. ## Restart the server from which you uninstalled the OpenStack Horizon plugin. </p>
                    <codeblock>systemctl restart httpd</codeblock>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
